cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MM, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving video recommender systems and search engines. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the concept of latent social impulses and how they can be used to measure a video's longevity. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the societal attention drawn by longevous videos. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper focuses on online video websites and their video content. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a semi-supervised learning task to predict the longevity scores of videos.
